# CORD_LIST_2_STARS_MSAW
Converts a list of coordinates and altitudes in a specific format to a vSTARS MSAW xml format that is easily inserted into the appropriate configuration file.

Required source file format:

Volume Name
MSAW Altitude
Cords
"END"

Example:

C1
6500
48.09423 -111.79670
48.07799 -111.79127
47.98509 -112.02195
47.99255 -112.03006
48.00883 -112.00142
48.03484 -111.95031
48.03841 -111.94315
48.05462 -111.90670
48.07074 -111.86637
END
